      },
      "date": "2013-12-11 07:43:19.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI am not exactly clear here,how come we have a freed element in hash? should not there be some refcounting to prevent this?\n\nWhat if some other user of hash would try to pick an element from hash and fail in the similar way?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "a228fad5149bf10e670361dc0de231583ed4c180",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 104,
        "name": "Niu Yawei",
        "email": "yawei.niu@intel.com",
        "username": "niu",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-12-12 02:54:42.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nOleg, since there is no other users, we don't want to add reference count or other serialising mechanism, that'll increase overhead unnecessarily. There are only two users for the hash: A to add ID in hash, B to check if specified ID is in hash.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
